<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-5584] Incorrect log size for topics larger than 2 GB</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5584</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;size&lt;/tt&gt; of a &lt;tt&gt;Log&lt;/tt&gt; is calculated incorrectly due to an Integer overflow. For large topics (larger than 2 GB) this value overflows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is easily observable in the reported metrics values of the path &lt;tt&gt;log.Log.partition.*.topic.&amp;lt;topicname&amp;gt;.Size&lt;/tt&gt; (see attached screenshot).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Moreover I think this breaks the size-based retention (via &lt;tt&gt;log.retention.bytes&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;retention.bytes&lt;/tt&gt;) of large topics as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am not sure on the recommended workflow, should I open a pull request on github with a fix?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
